Acknowledge
1) to make known, 2) to admit the truth or existence of, or 3) to express gratitude
Articulate
1) to speak clearly in distinct syllables or 2) well spoken
Assertion
declaration or affirmation
Attribute
1) to explain by indicating a cause or 2) to regard as a characteristic
Broach
to mention or suggest for the first time
Convey
1) to communicate, 2) to transport, 3) to transmit
Elicit
to bring out or call forth
Evoke
1) to bring to mind or 2) to produce
Indicate
1) to point out or point to or 2) to state or express briefly
Invoke
1) to cite in justification or 2) to appeal to earnestly
Promulgate
to announce or declare